
<div class="span3" >
  <%= render 'settings/navi' %>
</div>

<div class="span8" >

  <div class="row content_header_def" >
    Scheduler
  </div>

  <div class="span8 content" >

    <%= form_tag( settings_scheduler_path, :method => "post", :class => "form-horizontal") do  %>

      <p class="description">
        Here you can configure when VersionEye should perform several tasks.
      </p>

      <hr/>
      <p class="description">
        When should VersionEye send out the notification emails for software packages users follow directly?
      </p>

      <div class="control-group">
        <%= label_tag :schedule_follow_notifications, "Notifications", :class => "control-label", :for => "schedule_follow_notifications" %>
        <div class="controls">
          <%= text_field_tag :schedule_follow_notifications, @globalsetting['schedule_follow_notifications'], :id => "schedule_follow_notifications" %>
        </div>
      </div>


      <hr/>
      <p class="description">
        User projects an be monitored daily, weekly and monthly.
        When should VersionEye send out the notification emails for projects which are monitored <b>daily</b>?
        Use a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron#CRON_expression" target="_Cron">cron expression</a>. For example <b>15 9 * * *</b> for every day at 9:15 AM in the morning.
      </p>

      <div class="control-group">
        <%= label_tag :schedule_project_notification_daily, "Daily", :class => "control-label", :for => "schedule_project_notification_daily" %>
        <div class="controls">
          <%= text_field_tag :schedule_project_notification_daily, @globalsetting['schedule_project_notification_daily'], :id => "schedule_project_notification_daily" %>
        </div>
      </div>


      <hr/>
      <p class="description">
        User projects an be monitored daily, weekly and monthly.
        When should VersionEye send out the notification emails for projects which are monitored <b>weekly</b>?
        Use a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron#CRON_expression" target="_Cron">cron expression</a>. For example <b>15 11 * * 2</b> for every 2nd day of the week at 11:15 AM in the morning.
      </p>

      <div class="control-group">
        <%= label_tag :schedule_project_notification_weekly, "Weekly", :class => "control-label", :for => "schedule_project_notification_weekly" %>
        <div class="controls">
          <%= text_field_tag :schedule_project_notification_weekly, @globalsetting['schedule_project_notification_weekly'], :id => "schedule_project_notification_weekly" %>
        </div>
      </div>


      <hr/>
      <p class="description">
        User projects an be monitored daily, weekly and monthly.
        When should VersionEye send out the notification emails for projects which are monitored <b>monthly</b>?
        Use a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron#CRON_expression" target="_Cron">cron expression</a>. For example <b>1 11 1 * *</b> for every first day of the month at 11:01 AM in the morning.
      </p>

      <div class="control-group">
        <%= label_tag :schedule_project_notification_monthly, "Monthly", :class => "control-label", :for => "schedule_project_notification_monthly" %>
        <div class="controls">
          <%= text_field_tag :schedule_project_notification_monthly, @globalsetting['schedule_project_notification_monthly'], :id => "schedule_project_notification_monthly" %>
        </div>
      </div>


      <hr/>
      <p class="description">
        VersionEye Enterprise can fetch information from VersionEye.com about software packages in the VersionEye Enterprise database. That is especially useful for software packages not hosted in your network. When should VersionEye perform this partial sync?
        Use a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron#CRON_expression" target="_Cron">cron expression</a>. For example <b>17 2 * * *</b> for every day at 02:17 AM in the morning.
      </p>

      <div class="control-group">
        <%= label_tag :sync_db, "DB Sync", :class => "control-label", :for => "sync_db" %>
        <div class="controls">
          <%= text_field_tag :sync_db, @globalsetting['sync_db'], :id => "sync_db" %>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div class="control-group">
        <div class="control-label"></div>
        <div class="controls">
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-large btn-primary" >Save</button>
        </div>
      </div>

    <% end %>

  </div>
</div>

